Roles and responsibilities as O&M Supervisor LVP (2022 – present):
	Legal accountable person on site on behalf of the company for execution of all the work in a safe manner as per Shell Standards. 
	Execute AMS key work processes Permit to Work (PtW), Safe Isolations (SI) and Maintenance Execution (ME) are followed;
	Lead a team that consists of 2 Assistant Operations Supervisor, 4 Senior Operating Technicians and a Responsible Electrical Person;
	Ensure staff development, coaching and succession planning for staff in the direct reporting line;
	NAM Den Helder Representative for SodM.

The LVP is a highly important HSE critical role on site. In this role I am legal accountable that all activities are identified, prepared  to ensure a safe place of work for execution. During this period, I introduced two whiteboards to visualize our workflows for Unit T/A’s and waste management (PGS15) to be legally compliant. I also optimized the safeguarding procedure, with all relevant disciplines according to Shell Control Framework.

Roles and responsibilities as OMC (2020 – 2022):
	Primary interface between Operations & Maintenance;
	Screening, prioritization and approval of Corrective Maintenance;
	Validating break-in work and the impact on the week planning with the aim to achieve the Scheduled Attainment target;
	Identifying and escalating equipment deficiencies.

In this role I was the first OMC at Den Helder to create plan stability, and act as liaison between Operations and Maintenance. I also improved the link between Operations and Projects by cooperating with the commissioning engineer on planning. Finally, I introduced a new "standard text" to optimize information into the Z1 notifications. Taken together these measures led to significant increases in efficiency in our work processes.
